No CSS files needed - all Tailwind classes.

## Components Best Practices

### Do
- ✅ Use Tailwind classes for all styling
- ✅ Accept `brief: ClientBrief` as prop
- ✅ Map over arrays from brief (services, faqs, etc)
- ✅ Use semantic HTML elements
- ✅ Add `alt` text to images
- ✅ Make sections responsive (mobile-first)
- ✅ Use hover states and transitions
- ✅ Keep components focused and single-purpose

### Don't
- ❌ Don't import/use CSS files
- ❌ Don't hardcode business data
- ❌ Don't create global state (use props)
- ❌ Don't add unnecessary complexity
- ❌ Don't break the responsive layout
- ❌ Don't modify app/page.tsx to add new sections (add component instead)

## SEO & Metadata

**Automatic from JSON**:
- Page title: `{businessName} | {tagline}`
- Meta description: From description field
- Keywords: businessName, industry, location
- Open Graph: Image, title, description
- Twitter Card: All meta tags

All generated in `page.tsx` using `generateMetadata()`.

## Adding New Sections

To add a new section to the website:

1. **Create component**: `components/NewSection.tsx`
   ```typescript
   import { ClientBrief } from '@/lib/client-data'

   export function NewSection({ brief }: { brief: ClientBrief }) {
     return (
       <section className="py-20 lg:py-28 bg-white">
         {/* Your content here */}
       </section>
     )
   }
   ```

2. **Add to JSON schema**: Update `ClientBrief` interface in `lib/client-data.ts`

3. **Add to page**: Import and use in `app/page.tsx`
   ```typescript
   import { NewSection } from '@/components/NewSection'
   // Then in return:
   <NewSection brief={brief} />
   ```

## Common Tasks

### Change Colors
Edit Tailwind classes in components. No config needed - use inline classes.

### Add New Client
```bash
mkdir -p clients/new-name/images
cp clients/example-client/client-brief.json clients/new-name/
# Edit the JSON
```

### Change Content
Edit `clients/example-client/client-brief.json` - website updates on refresh.

### Add Local Images
1. Place in: `clients/example-client/images/hero.jpg`
2. Use in JSON: `"heroImage": "/clients/example-client/images/hero.jpg"`

### Modify Component Design
Edit component file in `/components/` - only change Tailwind classes, keep structure same.

